-- Deutsche Bank Hires Ronan Clarke From Nomura as Europe High-Yield Analyst
-- Kate Haywood
-- 2010-07-20T10:47:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/deutsche-bank-hires-ronan-clarke-from-nomura-as-europe-high-yield-analyst.html

          
          
             Deutsche Bank AG hired  Ronan Clarke ,
Nomura Holdings Inc.’s former head of high-yield credit research
for Europe, the Middle East and Africa, according to two people
familiar with the matter.  
 Clarke will join at the end of September as a London-based
analyst reporting to  Richard Phelan , head of high-yield
research, said the people, who declined to be identified before
an announcement. Clarke left Tokyo-based Nomura’s London office
less than nine months after joining. He was previously with
Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc in London.  
 Deutsche Bank spokeswoman  Louise Pancott  in London declined
to comment.  
